I was at Disney World not long ago. I was there with a good bit of my extended family as a sort of family reunion. We were having dinner in a restaurant that was part of one of the very upscale hotels - can't remember which one precisely - and I was sitting opposite the booths, meaning, my back was to the open walk space between tables.
Well, as you might imagine, being a Disney establishment, this place had costumed characters walking around. This one guy who was patrolling our area was dressed like Prince Charming... I believe from either Snow White or Sleeping Beauty. And he was in character too, of course.
As this was happening, I was kinda not involved in whatever conversation was happening at the time with my family, so I started absentmindedly checking shit on my phone. A Google notification made me look at my photos, which caused me to start scrolling through my saved ones. I came upon this picture: Isabelle from Animal Crossing and the Mayor. Yes, it was hmofa. It wasn't outright porn, but it was suggestive and pretty fucking weird by normie standards. I wasn't really thinking about the outside world so I just kinda stared at the pic for a moment. But then I abruptly heard a guy behind me start to say something and stop just as quickly.
I turned and it was fucking Prince Charming. The guy came up to the table, apparently wanted to interact with us, but saw what I was looking at and was shocked, I assume. And he just stared at me for a second. And that was genuinely one of the only moments in my life where I can really remember feeling the blood rushing to my face and my cheeks getting hot. I felt like such a retard.
Well apparently that was too much for him and he just kinda looked around and pretended like he hadn't said anything... pretended like he hadn't just tried to talk to us. He just slowly walked away as my family watched him and wondered wtf he had just tried to do. So that's a way hmofa has influenced my life.
